 📝 C Task Manager Project

A simple command-line task manager program in C developed collaboratively for our school syllabus project.



📂 Project Structure

main.c — contains the main menu and function calls.
Each function will be implemented in this file by different team members via separate branches.



👥 Team Members & Responsibilities

| Member Name | Feature(s) | Branch Name |
|:------------|:----------------|:---------------|
| [Nelly Makena ] | Project setup, main menu, merging PRs | main.C |
| [Mark] | add_task() | feature/add-task |
| [Scott] | list_tasks() | feature/list-task |
| [Kerry Erastus] | mark_done(), delete_task() | feature/mark-delete-task |



🛠️ How to Contribute

1. Clone the repo
   bash
   git clone <repo-link>
   cd <project-folder>


2.Create your branch

bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name


3.Work on your assigned function

4.Add, commit and push

bash
Copy
Edit
git add main.c
git commit -m "Implemented <your-function-name>()"
git push origin feature/your-feature-name


5.Create a Pull Request (PR) to main

6.Leader reviews and merges the PR


📌 Notes
Do not modify other members' functions or the main menu

Always pull the latest changes before starting new work:

bash
Copy
Edit
git pull origin main




